From March 15, 2020 in France, the Ministry of Soldarity and Health has mandated that in order to slow the spread of the virus, hygiene measures defined at the national level, must be observed in all places and in all circumstances.Hygiene measures include the following (Article 1):
-Regular hand washing with soap and water (access to which must be facilitated by the provision of single-use towels) or by hydro-alcoholic friction;
-systematically cover your nose and mouth when coughing or sneezing into your elbow;
-Blow your nose in a single-use handkerchief to be disposed of immediately in a wastebasket;
-Avoid touching your face, especially your nose, mouth and eyes;
-Masks must be worn systematically by all when the rules of physical distancing cannot be guaranteed.
Gatherings, meetings, activities and receptions which are not prohibited at this time must be organized while ensuring strict compliance with these measures.

