On 31 May 2020, the French National government announces that, the airport operator and the air carrier are required to inform passengers of the following hygiene and distancing measures by means of audible announcements, as well as terminal displays and information on board the aircraft. Hygiene measures are as follows:

- wash your hands regularly with soap and water (access to which must be facilitated with the provision of single-use towels) or by hydro-alcoholic friction;
- systematically cover your nose and mouth when coughing or sneezing into your elbow;
- blow your nose in a single-use tissue to be disposed of immediately in a trash can;
- avoid touching your face, especially your nose, mouth and eyes.
The airport operator and the air transport company are also required to provide access to a soap and water point or to hydro-alcoholic gel for passengers.

