From September 1st 2020, in France, Elisabeth Borne, ministry of labour announced that masks are mandatory in companies, offices, open-spaces, except in individual offices.  The cost of the mask, surgical or tissue, will now be borne by the employer. 
 UPDATE: UPDATE: As part of the strengthening of health measures, from March 24th, 2021, French government announced that the national protocol in enterprise is updated:

Asking employers to define action plans to minimize on-site presence of employees who can telework;
setting up, as far as possible, packed meals to be taken away and consumed at the workplace for all or part of the employees;
having lunch alone, leaving an empty space in front of you, and strictly respecting the 2 meter distancing rule between each person;
systematically adapting the opening hours for collective catering in order to limit as much as possible the number of people on site at the same time;
limiting car-sharing situations as far as possible and, if necessary, respecting barrier measures, in particular the wearing of masks;
reminding their employees of the rules applicable to the isolation of contact and symptomatic cases as well as the possibility of declareameli.fr as soon as symptoms appear, to benefit from a work stoppage.

